This paper deals with the problem of recommendation systems, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper proposes new methods for nonnegative matrix factorization (NMF) and compares them with classical algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses evaluation measures for recommendation systems, which is related to data mining (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper uses datasets from different domains, including movies, jokes, and foods, which suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB) and social networks (cs.SI).
